value.0: Tough hemp fibers are woven together to form a rough, yet rollable mattress.  Often place on the ground to keep the moisture from seeping through.  They usually have a worn, old woolen blanket rolled up inside  to use as a pillow or a cover.  Little comfort is achieved when resting on it, but keeps the user dry and warm enough to get a few hours of sleep and is often preferred to sleeping on the bare ground.
